<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Polly Blacker – Written evidence</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Polly Blacker – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I am a regular cyclist and walker.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I am also a volunteer </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Sustrans</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Ranger.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Walking in the Peak District, I have regularly had my walk disturbed significantly by off-</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">roading</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> vehicles of various sorts; 4-wheel drive cars, trail bikes, quad bikes (the worst incident was on </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Houndkirk</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> when we had moved to the side as a convoy of 4-wheel drive vehicles approached, the lead driver shouted at us: “Like walking on a road do you?” when we were by then in fact standing on a bank above the path.)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Apart from the noise and air pollution caused by off-</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">roading</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> vehicles, they carve up the surface of the path badly making walking and cycling very difficult – in fact cycling, unless on a mountain bike, has become impossible on some ‘green lanes’ in the Peak District.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Even where there are barriers to prevent entry to paths by off-</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">roading</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> vehicles these can often be got round – trail bikes and quad bikes can quite easily go through the normal barriers for cyclists; on Sunday 25</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> August 2013 while carrying out our regular </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Sustrans</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> route litter-pick and general check, 2 quads and a trail bike roared through </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Beeley</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Woods between </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Claywheels</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Lane and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Oughtibridge</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> in Sheffield so we reported this on 101 (incident number 511).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I would therefore request that you consider: </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">classifying as restricted byways all unsealed unclassified roads (UUCRs) (</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ie</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> green lanes)</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">downgrading all existing unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs) to restricted byway status</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">OR, or if this is seen as too draconian a measure, downgrading to restricted byway all unsealed UUCRs and BOATs in National Parks, Areas of Natural Beauty (AONBs) and where part of National Trails</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">provide</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> rights of appeal against refusals by highway authorities to make Traffic Regulation Orders excluding motor vehicles from green lanes.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">30 August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>